final_output_text: To underline text in OneNote, there are two methods to achieve this. Here's a step-by-step explanation of both methods:

**Method 0: Using the "B" Button**

1. First, locate the text you wish to underline in your OneNote page.
2. Next, right-click on the selected text. This will open a context menu.
3. From the context menu, click on the "B" button. This will underline the selected text.

**Method 1: Using the "U" Button**

1. First, locate the text you wish to underline in your OneNote page.
2. Next, select the text by highlighting it. You can do this by clicking and dragging your mouse over the text.
3. Once the text is highlighted, click on the "U" button on the top of the screen. This will underline the selected text.

